node.text: Why?? 😳🐶 He looks so cute but he’s really mean.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Mark Wahlberg on July 23, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, beard and outdoors.

node.text: Bullying and cruelty for any reason is wrong. We made this movie for the Joe Bells of the world. My hope is that you leave the theaters with more understanding and support for those around you: your child, your coworker, your community member. At the end of the day — no matter our differences — we are ALL human and deserving of love and compassion. ❤️🙏❤️ @joebellthemovie is in theaters now. #ThankYouJoeBell  www.joebellthemovie.com

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Mark Wahlberg on July 22, 2021. May be an image of 4 people, people standing and pool.

node.text: They never got me under! 😤🤣❤️

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Mark Wahlberg on July 22, 2021 tagging @christinejones2049. May be an image of text that says 'just watched the Joe Bell movie trailer. I've always been a huge fan, and you doing this movie means so much to me.l have always been acc”ting of my gay son from day one, but there are so many parents who are not. I'm just so thankful that this movie will be coming out! pray that it helps open the hearts and our minds of parents who are struggling to accept their children as they are! Thank you!'.

node.text: Powerful messages — thank you to Paul and the others tagged who have reached out. We love hearing how you’ve been moved by Joe Bell’s mission to honor his son and end bullying. Share your story with us using the hashtag #ThankYouJoeBell ❤️ @joebellthemovie www.joebellthemovie.com

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Mark Wahlberg on July 22, 2021 tagging @christinejones2049. May be an image of text that says 'just watched the Joe Bell movie trailer. I've always been a huge fan, and you doing this movie means so much to me.l have always been acc”ting of my gay son from day one, but there are so many parents who are not. I'm just so thankful that this movie will be coming out! pray that it helps open the hearts and our minds of parents who are struggling to accept their children as they are! Thank you!'.

Photo shared by Mark Wahlberg on July 22, 2021 tagging @heathermatson_. May be an image of text that says 'My child attempted suicide in January. They have come out as trans and will do everything in my power to protect them from the hate in the world. The preview made me oaw and hit me hard because live it. Thank you for bringing light to our LGBT kids'.

Photo shared by Mark Wahlberg on July 22, 2021 tagging @___camstagram___. May be an image of text that says 'Hi Mark. Our son came out to us as trans a few months ago. Thank you for spreading this message of the importance of loving our children for who they really are. This important, brave step forward is about THEIR journey, not ours. But they need us to put aside our self absorption and give them love and support. This is the biggest lesson my husband and have learned through this. Thank you again.'.

Photo by Mark Wahlberg on July 22, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'So excited for this Joe Bell movie. My sibling just came out as trans and pansexual august ast year and it's been a learning experience for everyone. I'm glad media is finally bringing to light the struggles they have but also the acceptance of the families and people that deal with this. Thank you so much. Huge fan.'.

Photo by Mark Wahlberg on July 22, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'I'm a young father with young daughter daughters.. my youngest has recently told me she's gay and couldn't be more proud of her or the living her true self.. your trailer brought tears to my eyes and guarantee it'll make our entire family cry.. you made us all cry for Boston and you're gonna do it again.. amazing man in an amazing role.. thank you Mark'.
